sequenceDiagram
    participant Browser as Browser
    participant Resolver as DNS Resolver<br/>1.1.1.1
    participant CDN_DNS as CDN Auth DNS<br/>Cloudflare NS
    participant Edge as CDN Edge PoP<br/>Nearest via Anycast
    participant Shield as Origin Shield<br/>Mid-Tier Cache
    participant Origin as Origin Server

    Note over Browser,Origin: Complete CDN Request Flow - Cache MISS then HIT

    Browser->>Resolver: DNS query: www.example.com
    Resolver->>CDN_DNS: Recursive query
    CDN_DNS-->>Resolver: A: 104.16.132.229 (Anycast IP)<br/>TTL: 300s
    Resolver-->>Browser: 104.16.132.229

    Note over Browser,Edge: TCP + TLS 1.3 Handshake (1 RTT)
    Browser->>Edge: SYN
    Edge-->>Browser: SYN-ACK
    Browser->>Edge: ACK + ClientHello
    Edge-->>Browser: ServerHello + Cert + Finished
    Browser->>Edge: Finished

    Browser->>Edge: GET /images/hero.jpg HTTP/2<br/>Accept-Encoding: br, gzip

    Note over Edge: Edge Processing Pipeline
    Edge->>Edge: 1. DDoS check (XDP/eBPF)
    Edge->>Edge: 2. WAF rules check
    Edge->>Edge: 3. Bot score evaluation
    Edge->>Edge: 4. Cache lookup: MISS

    Edge->>Shield: GET /images/hero.jpg<br/>(persistent connection)
    Shield->>Shield: Cache lookup: MISS

    Shield->>Origin: GET /images/hero.jpg<br/>(persistent connection pool)
    Origin-->>Shield: 200 OK<br/>Cache-Control: public, s-maxage=86400<br/>ETag: "a1b2c3"<br/>[245KB image]
    Shield->>Shield: Store in shield cache

    Shield-->>Edge: 200 OK + image
    Edge->>Edge: Store in edge cache<br/>Compress with Brotli

    Edge-->>Browser: HTTP/2 200 OK<br/>CF-Cache-Status: MISS<br/>Content-Encoding: br<br/>[compressed image]

    Note over Browser,Origin: Second Request - Cache HIT (no origin contact)

    Browser->>Edge: GET /images/hero.jpg HTTP/2
    Edge->>Edge: Cache lookup: HIT<br/>Age: 3600s, fresh (< 86400s)
    Edge-->>Browser: HTTP/2 200 OK<br/>CF-Cache-Status: HIT<br/>Age: 3600<br/>[cached image]

    Note over Browser,Origin: Cache HIT served in ~5ms vs ~200ms for MISS
